shared_text:
Indian Hills Athletics is with Abby Sweet and 15 others.
May 9, 2019 at 4:27 PM ¬∑

PROTECT THIS HOUSE! A berth to the NJCAA Division I National Softball Tournament will be on the line the next two days as No. 18-ranked Indian Hills (38-16) hosts No. 9-rated Crowder College (54-3) in the District J best-of-three series. Games one and two are scheduled for 2 p.m. and 4 p.m. Friday, and if a winner-take-all game three is needed, it will be at 2 p.m. on Saturday, back at R.L. Hellyer Field. IHCC brings a 21-game win streak into the series. The same two squads battled for a bid to nationals back in 2017 as the Warriors took game three in walk-off fashion, downing the visiting Roughriders, 2-1 in 11 innings. #WeAreHills #WarriorNation ü•é‚úåÔ∏è

Putnam County R-1 Schools
April 24, 2019 at 12:04 PM ¬∑

Congratulations to our KIRX/KRXL/KTUF JAMCO AWARDS ATHLETE OF THE WEEK, Miss Madison S from the Putnam County High School Track Team! Madi has been the top sprinter this spring for Putnam County, as well as a hurdler and long jumper. Madison took home four 1st place medals at both the Kirksville Invitational and the Truman State University High School Invitational track meets. She outdistanced the competition in the 100 Meter, 200 Meter, 300 Meter Hurdles, and the Long Jump at both events. Madison is looking to return to the state track meet again this spring as a junior. Congratulations again to Madison S of the Putnam County High School Track Team, our KIRX/KRXL/KTUF JAMCO AWARDS ATHLETE OF THE WEEK!

#PutnamProud #PutnamRuns #PutnamJumps #PutnamTrackAndField #JAMCOAthleteOfTheWeek

shared_text:
Putnam County Baseball
January 15, 2017 at 11:41 AM ¬∑

Putnam County Baseball is pleased to announce a very unique opportunity for our players, coaches, and fans. We are selling approximately 550 tickets to the Dodgers vs. Cardinals game on Memorial Day, May 29th, at 1:15pm. Immediately following the Cardinals game, the Putnam County Midgets and the Knox County Eagles will play at Busch Stadium on the same field as some of the biggest stars in the game.
Seats are located in the LF Loge and are substantially discounted at $25/ticket. 1 ticket allows access to both the Cardinals and Midgets games. You MUST attend Cardinals game to see Midgets game.
Tickets can be purchased from PC baseball players and coaches. Tickets are not currently in but we are accepting orders that will be filled upon arrival of tickets.
Donations are accepted for those who want to help but will not be able to make it to the game. Any little bit helps us make this dream come true.
Any questions can be directed toward Coach Bailey or Coach Robinson.
Thank you for supporting PC baseball and allowing us this memorable experience.

post_text: The Putnam County Booster club is selling raffle tickets for this fabulous t-shirt quilt! The quilt was custom made for the Booster Club by Marla Pace. It is 72 x 120 and will fit a twin or full size bed. It would also work great as a comfy throw at the foot of a queen or king bed. It would be the perfect gift for graduating Seniors or for any true blue Midget Fan! These quilts cost hundreds of dollars to have made. Raffle tickets may be purchased at the HS office or at any home basketball game for the cost of $5.00 per ticket. A winner will be drawn at halftime of the boys basketball game on February 18th. Good luck, and Let's Go Midgets!
